Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle with gradual curve of probably Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine brown, grey in patches.
Curator's comments: Benaki suggested to Grace per litteras 'looks Rhodian'; she thought of the 'Cretan' series - i.e. prow stamps, but this piece is not related to them save by the name Pausimachos. A piece from Kition is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1607)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
